    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Conspicuous Consumption</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Letter by Mike Mettler responds to June 15 article on increased use of entertainment devices for children in autos; says there is brave new world now on the open road</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I was interested to read both your article about entertainment systems for cars and the article about the growing complexity of car radios. Until June 9, the name of our magazine, which has been publishing for 14 years, was just Car Stereo Review. But because of the way the industry winds have been blowing, we will become Car Stereo Review's Mobile Entertainment this fall. As editor in chief, I can say that one thing's for sure: It's a brave new world out there on the open road.</p>
        <p>MIKE METTLER  New York City</p>
      </block>
